<dl id="n12114i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12114i">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12114i"> 114(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> P.P. stole an ox</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Le clerc qui avait d&eacute;rob&eacute; un cheval, un b&oelig;uf, une brebis, &eacute;tait passible d&apos;un je&ucirc;ne d&apos;un an, au pain et &agrave; l&apos;eau <br><font color="green">[The cleric who had stolen a horse, an ox, a sheep, was liable to a year-long fast, on bread and water]</font> <small> <a name="STCM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#STCM"><cite title="source">Saint Colomban</cite></a> (1905) 75</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
